      "href": "/upallnight/list/british-kitchen-sink-realism/",
      "user": "upallnight",
      "slug": "british-kitchen-sink-realism",
      "title": "British Kitchen Sink Realism",
      "desc": "From the sinks of working class industrial England, the social lens probed real life themes such as: abortion, divorce, homelessness, single motherhood, interracial sex, unemployment, poverty, and homosexuality.\n\nThrough the monotony of marriage, domestic life, and dead end jobs arose The Angry Young Man. Most often included a sink set piece but not a requirement.",
      "owner": "List by UpAllNight",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/sailordanae/list/british-kitchen-sink-drama/",
      "user": "sailordanae",
      "slug": "british-kitchen-sink-drama",
      "title": "British Kitchen Sink Drama",
      "desc": "An artistic movement in the late 50's and early 60's, kitchen sink dramas focused on social realism, poverty, working-class protagonists, and controversial issues. Anger, disillusionment, and dissatisfaction ruled the lives of these characters, the struggle to survive in an uncaring world. \n\nThis may or may not be a full list of these films.",
      "owner": "List by sailordanae PATRON",
      "tags": []
    },
    {
      "href": "/gclarke/list/british-kitchen-sink-realism-1959-1970/",
      "user": "gclarke",
      "slug": "british-kitchen-sink-realism-1959-1970",
      "title": "British Kitchen sink realism 1959-1970",
